    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This seems to work in current master, presumably as part of the window functions rewrite:\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [30]: pd.rolling_mean(df, window=-1) # yes, I know, deprecated\r\n[...]\r\nValueError: window must be non-negative\r\n\r\nIn [31]: df.rolling(window=-1)\r\n[...]\r\nValueError: window must be non-negative\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe only thing which seems a little surprising to me is that we catch the negative window at construction but the negative min_periods at evaluation:\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn [45]: df.rolling(window=1)\r\nOut[45]: Rolling [window=1,center=False,axis=0]\r\n\r\nIn [46]: df.rolling(window=1, min_periods=-2)\r\nOut[46]: Rolling [window=1,min_periods=-2,center=False,axis=0]\r\n\r\nIn [47]: df.rolling(window=1, min_periods=-2).sum()\r\n[...]\r\nValueError: min_periods must be >= 0\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut it's hard to get too worked up about that."
  },
